<ns436:section xmlns:ns436="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.referenceArchitectures.j2ee.frameworks.frameworks">

  <ns437:title xmlns:ns437="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Java EE frameworks</ns437:title>
  <ns438:para xmlns:ns438="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The Java Enterprise Edition (JEE) provides a reference architecture within
    which multi-tier enterprise applications are developed.
  </ns438:para>  
  
  <ns439:section xmlns:ns439="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns440:title xmlns:ns440="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">What is a Java EE framework?</ns440:title>
    <ns441:para xmlns:ns441="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The specification provides a range of standard APIs which must be implemented by
      Java EE <ns442:emphasis xmlns:ns442="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">frameworks</ns442:emphasis>. But what is a Java EE framework?
      <ns443:blockquote xmlns:ns443="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns444:para xmlns:ns444="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns445:emphasis xmlns:ns445="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        A Java EE framework is a tool that can host systems built according to the Java EE reference architecture.
      </ns445:emphasis></ns444:para></ns443:blockquote>    
    </ns441:para>
  </ns439:section>
  
  <ns446:section xmlns:ns446="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns447:title xmlns:ns447="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Example frameworks</ns447:title>
    <ns448:para xmlns:ns448="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      There are many frameworks available which implement this
      reference architecture. Some of these are vendor solutions like
      <ns449:itemizedlist xmlns:ns449="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns450:listitem xmlns:ns450="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns451:para xmlns:ns451="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns452:emphasis xmlns:ns452="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">BEA WebLogic</ns452:emphasis></ns451:para></ns450:listitem>
        <ns453:listitem xmlns:ns453="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns454:para xmlns:ns454="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns455:emphasis xmlns:ns455="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">IBM Websphere</ns455:emphasis></ns454:para></ns453:listitem>
        <ns456:listitem xmlns:ns456="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns457:para xmlns:ns457="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns458:emphasis xmlns:ns458="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Oracle Application Server</ns458:emphasis></ns457:para></ns456:listitem>
        <ns459:listitem xmlns:ns459="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns460:para xmlns:ns460="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns461:emphasis xmlns:ns461="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Borland Application Server</ns461:emphasis></ns460:para></ns459:listitem>
      </ns449:itemizedlist>
    </ns448:para>
    <ns462:para xmlns:ns462="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      In addition to these vendor solutions there are also a number of open-source frameworks
      that realise the Java EE reference architecture, including
      <ns463:itemizedlist xmlns:ns463="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns464:listitem xmlns:ns464="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns465:para xmlns:ns465="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JBoss,</ns465:para></ns464:listitem>
        <ns466:listitem xmlns:ns466="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns467:para xmlns:ns467="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Glassfish,</ns467:para></ns466:listitem>
        <ns468:listitem xmlns:ns468="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns469:para xmlns:ns469="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Jonas,</ns469:para></ns468:listitem>
        <ns470:listitem xmlns:ns470="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns471:para xmlns:ns471="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          and Apache Geronimo.
        </ns471:para></ns470:listitem>
      </ns463:itemizedlist>
    </ns462:para>
  </ns446:section>
  
</ns436:section>